-- Stockerbroker Charles Stanley Managed Funds Decline on Market Uncertainty
-- Sakshi Sharma
-- 2010-07-29T06:59:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/stockbroker-charles-stanley-managed-funds-decline-on-market-uncertainty-.html

          
          
             Charles Stanley Plc , a U.K.
stockbroker and fund manager, reported a 4.7 percent decline in
funds under management in the fiscal first quarter “against a
background of continued market uncertainty.”  
 Funds under management dropped to 12.2 billion pounds
($19 billion) on June 30 from 12.8 billion pounds at the end of
March, the London-based company said in a statement today.
Revenue rose 11 percent to 28.9 million pounds.  
 The benchmark FTSE 100 Index fell about 13% during
the quarter.  
